727109f-a.text: Junction Boulevard (foreground), west side, at Thirty-Fifth Ave., showing a Northwest view of the Charles P. Leverich house. About March 1923. Eugene L. Armbruster Collection.

727110f-c.text: Junction Boulevard (foreground), west side, at Thirty-Fifth Ave., showing a view N.W. of the Charles P. Leverich house. Eugene L. Armbruster states this to be also the Col. Edward Leverich house and that Chas. P., his son, was born here in 1809. This information was given by one Van Rieper. However, the original home of Col. Edward Leverich was sold by him about 1820 to one Hendrickson, who in turn sold in 1851 to John and George Elliot. This house was located on the south side of Thirty-Seventh Ave. between 112th and 114th Street and was demolished prior to 1915. See the History of Queens County and other views in out files on this house. This is a set of three views. The first two are viewed northwest and the last northwest. March 1923. View 2: March 1924. View 3: March 1925. Eugene L. Armbruster Collection.
